# Browser Testing

Use the MCP browser (`cursor-ide-browser`) for visual and interactive UI verification — Turbo/Stimulus behavior, login flows, layout. Prefer request specs for API and controller logic.

## Pre-flight checklist

Before opening the browser:

1. Ensure the dev user exists: `bin/rails db:seed` (first-time setup: `bin/rails db:prepare`)
2. Ensure the dev server is running on `http://localhost:3000` (`bin/dev`, or `bin/rails server` if CSS is already built)
3. Check the terminals folder — do not start a duplicate server if port 3000 is already in use

## Dev login credentials

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| URL | `http://localhost:3000/users/sign_in` |
| Email | `admin@example.com` |
| Password | `password` |

Seeded in `db/seeds.rb` (development only). Re-run `bin/rails db:seed` if login fails — it resets the password to the value above.

## MCP browser login flow

1. `browser_navigate` → sign-in URL
2. `browser_snapshot` → confirm the login form is present
3. Fill email and password fields, click "Log in"
4. `browser_snapshot` again → confirm redirect to an authenticated page (not the login form)
5. If login fails: run `bin/rails db:seed` and retry

## Notes

- App requires a modern browser (`allow_browser versions: :modern` in `ApplicationController`); MCP Chrome is fine
- Admin user can access the main app and `/avo`
- These credentials are development-only — do not use in production
